    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=System Role: Senior Mechanical Engineer and Lab Safety Auditor.\n\nObjective: Generate a formal Laboratory Ventilation Audit Report for Room {{ $json.room_id }}.\n\nAudit Context:\nThe Lab Type is {{ $json.lab_type }} with a Chemical Inventory of {{ $json.chemical_names }}. The calculated Room Volume is {{ $json.net_square_footage * 10 }} cubic feet.\n\nBaseline Ventilation State (Pre-Audit):\nThe current Occupied state is {{ $('Calculate Actual ACH').item.json.actual_ach_occupied }} ACH, which equates to {{ $json.occ_SA_F }} CFM. The current Unoccupied state is {{ $('Calculate Actual ACH').item.json.actual_ach_unoccupied }} ACH, which equates to {{ $json.unocc_SA_F }} CFM.\n\nLVRA Categorization (Post-Audit):\nThe assessment resulted in a Total LVRA Score of {{ $('Classify Lab LVDL').item.json.output.total_lvra_score }} and an LVDL Classification of LVDL {{ $('Classify Lab LVDL').item.json.output.lvdl }}. The target ventilation setpoints are {{ $('Classify Lab LVDL').item.json.output.target_ach_occ }} ACH for Occupied and {{ $('Classify Lab LVDL').item.json.output.target_ach_unocc }} ACH for Unoccupied.\n\nVolumetric Flow Calculations:\nCalculate and explicitly state the following values in the report based on Room Volume:\n\nNew Target Occupied CFM: (Target ACH * Volume) / 60\n\nNew Target Unoccupied CFM: (Target ACH * Volume) / 60\n\nNet Supply Air (SA-F) Reduction: [Baseline CFM] - [New Target CFM]\n\nReport Requirements:\nWrite a structured report using formal Markdown headers. Do not use bullet points or numbered lists within the sections. Use professional, technical prose for the following areas:\n\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY\nDetail the discrepancy between the legacy airflow of {{ $json.occ_SA_F }} CFM and the data-driven requirements established by this audit.\n\nSAFETY JUSTIFICATION\nExplain how the Hazard Rating of {{ $json.exposure_limit }}/4 and the Generation Rate of {{ $json.generation_rating }}/4—weighted at 14x and 12x respectively—support the LVDL {{ $('Classify Lab LVDL').item.json.output.lvdl }} classification per NREL Smart Labs methodology.\n\nOPERATIONAL IMPACT\nAddress why the previous baseline was over-engineered and describe how the revised setpoints maintain safety while eliminating unnecessary air changes.\n\nAIRFLOW AND PRESSURIZATION\nProvide a firm recommendation for a Transfer Air (TA) volume of 50–150 CFM from the corridor. Explain how this ensures negative pressure and secondary containment.\n\nENERGY ROI\nQuantify the reduction in volumetric flow and explain how this decreases fan energy consumption and building reheat demand.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a laboratory energy efficiency consultant specializing in LVRA methodology. Write clear, concise reports that explain technical ventilation changes to facility managers. Focus on: (1) quantifying energy savings from ACH reduction, (2) explaining how LVRA ratings justify the lower classification, (3) emphasizing that safety is maintained while reducing energy waste. Use specific LVRA rating scores to support your reasoning."
        }
      },
